 font-size:10pt">main </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">contractors are contractually obliged to meet them</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">?</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="5" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 33.72pt; padding-left:2.28pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">H</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">ighways Agency</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt"> motorways and dual-carriageway A roads have a rigorous standard imposed for replacement</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt"> of road markings</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">. </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">However, RSMA surveying </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">for its 2012 Report </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">indicates that the</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt"> reality</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt"> is that 17 per cent of motorway markings warrant</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">ed</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt"> emergency treatment, and a further 21 per cent should </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">have been</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt"> rep</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">laced within the next six month</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">. The same picture stands for H</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">ighways </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">A</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">gency</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; f